search:.NET MVC IdentityServer4 Advanced.content:
- Install IdentityServer4 via NuGet: `dotnet add package IdentityServer4`
- Configure IdentityServer4 in `Startup.cs`:
  ```csharp
  services.AddIdentityServer()
          .AddInMemoryClients(Config.Clients)
          .AddInMemoryIdentityResources(Config.IdentityResources)
          .AddInMemoryApiResources(Config.ApiResources);
  ```
- Add OpenID Connect authentication to MVC app:
  ```csharp
  services.AddAuthentication(options =>
      {
          options.DefaultAuthenticateScheme = CookieAuthenticationDefaults.AuthenticationScheme;
          options.DefaultSignInScheme = CookieAuthenticationDefaults.AuthenticationScheme;
          options.DefaultChallengeScheme = OpenIdConnectDefaults.AuthenticationScheme;
      })
      .AddCookie()
      .AddOpenIdConnect("oidc", "IdentityServer4", options =>
      {
          options.Authority = "https://localhost:5001";
          options.RequireHttpsMetadata = false;
          options.ClientId = "mvc";
          options.SaveTokens = true;
      });
  ```
- Ensure `appsettings.json` contains IdentityServer4 configuration:
  ```json
  "IdentityServer": {
    "Clients": [
      {
        "ClientId": "mvc",
        "ClientName": "MVC Client",
        "AllowedGrantTypes": ["authorization_code", "refresh_token"],
        "RedirectUris": ["/signin-oidc" ],
        "PostLogoutRedirectUris": ["/signout-callback-oidc" ]
      }
    ]
  }
  ```
- Run IdentityServer4 and MVC app on different ports to avoid conflicts.
